Text.Value: That doesn't lessen your victory. Well done.
I had plenty of help.
That you're an independent True Soul, and you saved this place from Ketheric Thorm. The stories you must be able to tell.
I was hoping to get a quiet moment with you, actually. There are some things I thought you might care to know. Perhaps I could drop by your camp later?
There's much I'd like to discuss with you, actually. Perhaps I could join you in your camp later?
I'll make it brief. Cleric's honour.
I don't think so.
A little time to rest and reflect, and I'll be ready to go at it anew. What say you?
I'd like to hear why you lied to me about being Ketheric's daughter.
You did it. I knew you would.

EditorData.logicalname: NIGHTSONG DEAD, met Isobel in HAV

Text.Value: Yet you don't seem glad.
I'd like that.
As would I. I'll see you later. Looking forward to it.
My camp's a little crowded already.
To be perfectly frank, I'm exhausted. It feels a bit as though I've been dropped into another dimension.
It's not over yet. A nautiloid is on its way to Baldur's Gate.
Why wait?
Ah! It's you, isn't it? You're the talk of this place, you know. I'm Isobel.

EditorData.logicalname: NIGHTSONG DEAD, has not met Isobel

Text.Value: And you. If what they say about you is true, you're the only reason most of us are alive.
Nice to meet you.
It's actually... quite a story. One I'd love to take a little time to share with you. Perhaps I could visit your camp later - a drink and a fire might help the tale.
What have you heard?
Good. Very good. Until then. And thank you, if I haven't said it yet.
Oh, I am. It's a momentous day. I suppose I need to catch my breath or the momentum will outpace me.
Where did you come from?
All right. See you later.
Take it easy, hmm? You deserve it.
You deserve to know that much - and more.
Pity. But I suppose you have your path, and I have mine. Perhaps they'll meet again. I won't rue the day.
Gods. One day, you go to sleep and everything's square. Then you wake up, and it's a dodecahedron. With tentacles.

Synopsis: The player has an opportunity to catch up with Isobel if she survived Act 2, but Nightsong died
